            <Summary>In June 2013, the North Indian states of Uttarakhand and Himachal Pradesh, some regions of Western Nepal and their adjoining areas experienced heavy rainfall that triggered devastating floods and landslides. As of 29 June 2013, more than 1,000 people have died with many more missing. Damage to bridges and roads left over 70,000 pilgrims and tourists trapped in various places. The Indian Air Force, the Army and paramilitary troops have evacuated more than 100,000 people from the flood hit areas.</Summary>
