            <Summary>Manmohan Singh (born 26 September 1932) is the 13th and current Prime Minister of India. Singh holds a doctorate in economics from Oxford university, and has served as an advisor to the Ministry of Foreign Trade, India (1966-69), Governer of the Reserve Bank of India (1982-85) and Deputy Chairman of the Planning Commission (1985-87), before being appointed the Minister of Finance in the Indian cabinet in 1991. As the Minister of finance, Singh carried out several structural reforms that liberalised India's economy. In 2004, Singh was elected as the Prime Minister of India. His government has since executed several key legislations and projects including the Rural Health Mission, Unique Identification Authority, Rural Employment Guarantee scheme and the Right to Information Act.</Summary>
